-- Family Dollar December same-store sales down 0.7 pct
-- 
-- Thu Jan 10, 2008 8:46am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/10/us-usa-retailsales-familydollar-idUSWNAS615520080110

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Discount store chain Family Dollar Stores Inc ( FDO.N ) said on Thursday that sales at stores open at least a year fell 0.7 percent in December and predicted that January same-store sales would be flat. 

 Analysts, on average, had been expecting the company to post a December same-store sales decrease of 1.9 percent, according to Reuters Estimates. Family Dollar, which had forecast December same-store sales to be flat or down slightly, said total sales for the five weeks ended January 6 rose 2.5 percent to $816.6 million from $796.7 million a year earlier. (Reporting by  Alexandria Sage , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)